"Kolomyts E.G.","Prediction of influence of global warming on biological cycle and carbon balance in forest ecosystems of the Volga River Basin",2008,"Russian Meteorology and Hydrology","33","7",,"430","440",,,10.3103/S1068373908070042,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-52749094547&partnerID=40&md5=360b296bc45f8dfc6fd332744e9c4545","Institute of Ecology of the Volga River Basin, Russian Academy of Sciences, ul. Komzina 10, Tolyatti 445003, Russian Federation","Kolomyts, E.G., Institute of Ecology of the Volga River Basin, Russian Academy of Sciences, ul. Komzina 10, Tolyatti 445003, Russian Federation","The gradient (ordination) analysis was used to find the tendencies and the rate of changes in discrete parameters of the cycle of forest phytomasses accompanying a growing thermoarid climatic trend. The prognostic estimates of biotic regulation of the carbon cycle by forest biogeocenoses according to the HadCM3 (version A2) climatic scenarios, describing the most powerful coming global warming, are presented. © Allerton Press, Inc. 2008.",,"Ecosystems; Carbon balances; Carbon cycling; Climatic scenarios; Discrete parameters; Forest ecosystems; River basins; Global warming; carbon balance; forest ecosystem; global warming; gradient analysis; phytomass; Eurasia; Russian Federation; Volga Basin",,,,,,"Gorshkov, V.G., (1995) Physical and Biological Bases of Life Stability, , (VINITI, Moscow) [in Russian]; Izrael, Yu.A., (1984) Ecology and Environmental Monitoring, , (Gidrometeoizdat, Leningrad) [in Russian]; Isaev, A.S., Korovin, G.N., ""Carbon in the Forests of Northern Eurasia"" (1999) Carbon Rotation in Russia. NTP ""Global Changes in Environment and Climate"", , in (RF Ministry of Sciences and Technologies, Moscow) [in Russian]; Kobak, K.I., (1988) Biotic Elements of Carbon Cycle, , (Gidrometeoizdat, Leningrad) [in Russian]; Kolomyts, E.G., ""Organization and Stability of Coniferous Forests Ecosystems at the Boreal Echotone of the Russian Plain"" (19